      "body": "Important architectural note for this ticket: generated context is not the canonical memory store.\n\nThe scripts here should rebuild a current-turn projection from canonical sources in knowledge / memory / plan. If the scripts become their own source of truth, the separation collapses and drift returns.\n\nSo the goal is:\n\n- source of truth in files with clear ownership\n- generated context as a view over that state\n- no stale copied context files unless they are explicitly generated outputs",
